Title: Dark
Actors: Nicolas Cage, Irène Jacob, Anton Yelchin
Plot: Paul Schrader was not allowed to come out with the version he desired for "Dying of the Light". He took the studio cut and modified it with his artistic license to achieve a closer version of the vision he had. "Dark" is a more aptly named film that focuses on CIA agent Evan Lake's last mission as he slowly begins to lose his mind from dementia/Alzheimer's.

Title: Sigmund Freud, un juif sans Dieu
Actors: Mathieu Amalric, Jeanne Balibar, Catherine Deneuve
Plot: Using rare archive images and his letters, a portrait of Sigmund Freud revealing his relationship with his family and friends.
